This paper deals with a security protocol for key exchange, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the security of the protocol against active attacks. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of computer networks (cs.NI), computer security and privacy (cs.CC), and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) as these fields often involve the use of secure key exchange protocols.
